cs.NI, cs.HC, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.CR

This paper involves using wireless network measurements to estimate breathing rate and location, which falls under the category of networked sensing and monitoring. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses applications in health care and security, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves developing a method to estimate breathing rate despite motion interference, which could fall under cs.MA (Machine Learning) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
